stanzas.text:
All glory to GOD be given;
For so good His great Love Divine;
Trusting He's Almighty to save,
Pledge thyself always to His care.

FATHER, Thy children we are,
Feed us with Thy Living bread;
For to Thee we leave our care;
Thou knowest our daily need.

GOD, I will keep Thy divine light
To guide my faulty steps to Thee;
Lest I wander away from Thee;
For peace have they who bear Thy Light.

LORD, it is our choice to be Thine;
Whatever may befall us;
And when the hour of trial comes,
We will call on Thee for help.

LORD, without Thee our hope is vain;
In Thy absence all is pain;
Thy presence is our joy and peace
O in this world void of ease!

Fill me with Thy Love Divine;
Fill me with Thy Light to Shine;
Let my heart rejoice for'er,
Christ my gracious Defender.

CHRIST the Light---Bless-ed Saviour.
Risen Lord, our Counsellor;
Shew Thy Light in all we care.

Christ---the Dayspring from above;
Lord, fill our hearts with Thy Love;
And ill thoughts from us remove.

As we part from this gath'ring,
Bid us home with Thy Blessing;
Christ the Light---O Gracious King!

LORD Jesus, now Thy holy Name we Praise;
We assemble here for Thy precious word;
We've come with unshaken hearts Thee to praise;
With purity of heart flowing with joy.

O leave me not gracious Jesus;
Lord incline Thy ears to my cries;
And make straight all my crooked ways
To serve Thee with clean thoughts for'er.

I am Thine, and Thou art mine;
Most belov-ed Gracious Christ;
Thou hast taught me I should know---
‘I am Thine and Thou art mine'.

The Spirit and the Bride say “Come”!;
And he that heareth say “Come”!;
Trust in Jesus, He'll make you free,
Ye shall indeed be saved.

Now leave me not O LORD;
Be not far from me my GOD

Deliver us from all our sins.

O Salem Land, the Land of joy;
The Bless-ed shore---my glorious love;
Here will my praise to GOD abound
On that beautiful Salem Land.

Welcome! Wonderful Counsellor And Mighty God.
In righteousness hast Thou come to judge This profane world;
And gather Thy chosen ones by grace, Into Thy Kingdom;
They shall be with Thee for evermore.

Brethren, come to our LORD with joy;
Come to Him with cheerful hearts;
For His blessings shall never fade.
Let us all rejoice and sing.

Long suffereth charity.
It is kind without envy;
And it vaunteth not itself;
Nor doth it puff up itself;
Doth not behave unseemly,
And it thinketh not evil.

(Duet) Remember now thy Creator
In the days of thy youth;
While the evil days come not.
